# 3. Separate Descriptive EDA from Model-Selection EDA

## Current Problem

The notebook uses the complete dataset to determine:

- selected lags
- selected rolling windows
- seasonal months
- transformation strategy
- minimum-history thresholds
- stable-brand inclusion
- feature relevance

This means validation and test outcomes indirectly influence modelling decisions.

## Why This Is Leakage

Even when individual lag features only use past observations, selecting those features because they correlate strongly with future validation or test outcomes constitutes model-selection leakage.

The following decisions must be based only on training data:

- imputation parameters
- scaling parameters
- transformation selection
- lag selection
- rolling-window selection
- outlier thresholds
- feature pruning
- category encoding
- brand selection rules
- hyperparameter tuning

