# 8. Decomposition Model Selection Is Invalid

## Current Problem

The notebook compares residual variance from:

- additive decomposition
- multiplicative decomposition

and selects the model with the smaller numeric variance.

## Why This Is Invalid

Additive residuals are measured in sales units.

Multiplicative residuals are typically ratios or proportional deviations.

The two residual variances therefore exist on different scales and cannot be directly compared.

A multiplicative decomposition will often have numerically smaller residual variance simply because the residuals are dimensionless.

## Better Comparison

Compare:

```text
additive decomposition on raw sales
```

with:

```text
additive decomposition on log-transformed sales
```

Alternatively, compare resulting forecasting performance on the same target scale.

The decision should consider whether seasonal amplitude increases with series level.

If high-volume series exhibit larger seasonal swings, a multiplicative structure or log transformation may be appropriate.

## Aggregation Concern

Decomposition of aggregate sales may hide different patterns across brands and markets.

Aggregate decomposition should therefore be descriptive and should not directly determine panel-level feature engineering.

