# 12. Distribution May Cause Contemporaneous Leakage

## Current Finding

`weighted_dist` appears strongly associated with sales.

This may be useful, but only if the feature is available when the forecast is made.

## Availability Question

When predicting sales for month `t+1`, is weighted distribution for month `t+1` already known?

If not, using contemporaneous future distribution creates leakage.

## Defensible Alternatives

Use:

```text
lagged weighted distribution
```

or:

```text
planned future distribution
```

if it is genuinely known before the forecast date.

Other possibilities:

- separately forecast distribution
- use distribution scenarios
- use distribution contracts or plans
- use previous-month distribution
- use rolling distribution trends

Every predictor should receive a feature-availability classification:

| Feature | Known at forecast time? | Allowed form |
|---|---:|---|
| Previous sales | Yes | Lagged |
| Month | Yes | Current/future |
| Holiday calendar | Yes | Current/future |
| Planned distribution | Possibly | Current/future if confirmed |
| Actual future distribution | No | Exclude |
| Actual future promotion | No unless planned | Exclude or use plan |
| Brand identity | Yes | Static |
| Market identity | Yes | Static |

