# 13. Correlation Should Not Be Interpreted Causally

## Current Risk

Statements such as:

```text
distribution matters
promotions work
promotions harm sales
```

cannot be established using pairwise correlation.

Observed correlations may be affected by:

- reverse causality
- confounding
- brand size
- market size
- seasonality
- planned commercial actions
- distribution allocation
- product lifecycle

For example, high-selling brands may receive broader distribution.

This does not mean distribution has no predictive value, but the interpretation must remain predictive rather than causal.

## Recommended Language

Use:

```text
The variables are associated at the observed data grain.
Their incremental predictive value and availability at forecast time
must be evaluated through temporal validation.
```

